comments.text:
struct wrapping `http.ResponseWriter` and `http.NewResponseController`. Tracks state (idle/streaming/completed). `WriteEvent` serializes `api.StreamEvent` as `event: {type}
data: {json}

`, detects terminal events and sends `data: [DONE]

`. `WriteResponse` writes complete JSON response. `Flush` delegates to ResponseController. Enforces mutual exclusion between WriteEvent and WriteResponse. Returns error after terminal event. (FR-007, FR-008, FR-009, FR-010, FR-011, FR-012, FR-020)

test WriteResponse produces correct JSON with `Content-Type: application/json`. Test WriteEvent produces correct SSE format (`event: {type}
data: {json}

`). Test terminal event followed by `data: [DONE]

`. Test WriteEvent after terminal returns error. Test WriteResponse after WriteEvent returns error (mutual exclusion). Test Flush delegates correctly. Test SSE headers (Cache-Control, Connection). (SC-001, SC-003)
